The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump addressing a shooting in Odessa, Texas and Hurricane Dorian. The President expresses condolences to the victims and their families of the shooting and commends the actions of local law enforcement. He also emphasizes the need to work with Congress to address mass attacks and reduce violent crime. Regarding Hurricane Dorian, the President thanks government officials and expresses concern about the size and potential impact of the storm. He assures that the federal government is prepared to assist with response and recovery operations and urges those in the storm's path to heed evacuation orders. The President also discusses efforts to bring in fuel and support first responders.